body: very curious how you are using `gsed` with `hack/local-up-cluster.sh` ...

> very curious how you are using `gsed` with `hack/local-up-cluster.sh` ...

My environment is Mac OS X, I run ``sed_help`` command on terminal got below error.
```
sed: illegal option -- -
usage: sed script [-Ealn] [-i extension] [file ...]
       sed [-Ealn] [-i extension] [-e script] ... [-f script_file] ... [file ...]
```
```
sed_help="$(LANG=C sed --help 2>&1)"
  if echo "${sed_help}" | grep -q "GNU\|BusyBox"; then
    SED="sed"
  elif command -v gsed &>/dev/null; then
    SED="gsed"
  else
    kube::log::error "Failed to find GNU sed as sed or gsed. If you are on Mac: brew install gnu-sed." >&2
    return 1
  fi
```

> My environment is Mac OS X, I run sed_help command on terminal got below error.

hack/local-up-cluster.sh does not support mac, that's the curiousity :sweat_smile:
